Your task is to implement a **Signed Deployable Artifact Reporting Solution**.

## What auditors want

Auditors want to know:

**“Out of the artifacts that can actually be deployed to the platform, which ones are signed and which ones are not?”**

Not just:

```text
80% artifacts are signed
```

They need details like:

```text
Which artifact?
Which version?
Which team?
Which application?
Which technology?
Which build?
Which environment?
Who signed it?
When was it signed?
Which key/certificate was used?
```

## Simple example

A platform has these deployable artifacts:

| Artifact             | Technology  | Team     | Build              | Environment | Signed |
| -------------------- | ----------- | -------- | ------------------ | ----------- | ------ |
| payment-api:1.2.5    | Docker      | Payments | Jenkins #451       | Prod        | Yes    |
| claims-service:3.1.0 | Docker      | Claims   | GitHub Actions #88 | Prod        | No     |
| member-ui:2.0.4      | npm/package | Member   | Jenkins #210       | Dev         | Yes    |

Auditor question:

```text
Show me all deployable prod artifacts that are unsigned.
```

Dashboard answer:

```text
claims-service:3.1.0 is deployable to prod but not signed.
```

That is the real requirement.

