## How to collect the data

You collect data from multiple sources.

### Source 1: JFrog Artifactory

Use Artifactory APIs to pull:

```text
artifact name
repo
path
checksum
created date
artifact properties
build info
```

### Source 2: JFrog Build Info

Use build info to map artifact back to:

```text
build number
pipeline
Git commit
branch
CI/CD job
module
dependencies
```

### Source 3: Signing metadata

Pull or detect signing data from:

```text
JFrog signing metadata
artifact properties
cosign signature
checksum/signature files
certificate/key metadata
```

### Source 4: Platform / deployment source

To know whether an artifact is deployable, collect from:

```text
Kubernetes manifests
Helm charts
deployment pipelines
release records
GitOps repo
Argo CD / Harness / Jenkins deployment jobs
```

This separates normal stored artifacts from **real deployable artifacts**.

